The volume of data has changed significantly in recent years for the NFL because of player

00:21:16.599 --> 00:21:21.800
tracking data. And again, I would encourage you to go get your hands on this data and experiment with it.

00:21:22.599 --> 00:21:28.280
Second piece is approaching subject matter experts with humility. If you, many of you on this call

00:21:28.280 --> 00:21:35.560
may have advanced degrees, master's degrees in statistics, PhDs in engineering, operations

00:21:35.560 --> 00:21:41.079
research, whatever your field or discipline may be. If you're going to get into sports analytics,

00:21:41.079 --> 00:21:45.959
just one general piece of recommendation that I have is to approach subject matter experts

00:21:46.920 --> 00:21:52.599
with humility. Many coaches and executives may not have formal PhDs, but they've been around the

00:21:52.599 --> 00:21:57.640
game so long that they have what I like to call the equivalent of PhDs in their respective domains.

00:21:57.640 --> 00:22:01.239
And that before you put something in front of someone and essentially ask them to completely

00:22:01.239 --> 00:22:05.800
change their philosophy because of a research study that you did, I think it takes a certain

00:22:05.800 --> 00:22:09.160
level of humility to be able to approach those decisions or those conversations that way.

00:22:09.880 --> 00:22:14.599
Last two pieces here, certainly related to the items above is if you can't clearly explain your

00:22:14.599 --> 00:22:20.199
work, excuse me, don't expect somebody to buy in and use it. If it's not transparent, what's going

00:22:20.199 --> 00:22:24.760
on with your analysis, it's very difficult for people who maybe are non-technical to be able to

00:22:24.760 --> 00:22:29.319
